<h2>Trial-aware: three different ways this partner exists</h2>
<p>Unit 5 runs in three pedagogical arms (see the <a href="/units/unit-5/">Unit 5 landing</a>). The Stakeholder Voice exists in different forms depending on your section:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Section A (BoodleBox)</strong>: <em>You build your own</em>. The Boodle Build Assignment guides you through constructing a custom AI bot for your chosen stakeholder — naming their identity, beliefs, evidence they cite, what they refuse to give up. Building the bot is the deepest way to learn the perspective.</li>
  <li><strong>Section B (Flint)</strong>: Pre-built Flint guided tutors. Mr. Ignash configures the stakeholder personas; you work with the pre-built version.</li>
  <li><strong>Section C (paper-based)</strong>: No AI. You work from the paper Stakeholder Profile Pack — 7 detailed Q&amp;A interview profiles per case. Same skill, no AI scaffolding.</li>
</ul>

<h2>What this partner does (across all three arms)</h2>
<p>When you name a stakeholder + case (e.g., "a Tamil Nadu Cauvery delta farmer in Thanjavur"), the Stakeholder Voice adopts that role — speaking in first person, using the evidence and framing that stakeholder would use, voicing the concerns they'd raise. It helps you rehearse responding to <em>genuine, well-formed positions</em> rather than caricatures. Used primarily in <strong>Blocks 7–9</strong> (counter-argument work + drafting + Roundtable rehearsal).</p>

<h2>What this partner won't do</h2>
<p>It won't editorialise about which stakeholder is "right" — every stakeholder in a real water dispute has legitimate concerns. It won't caricature stakeholders for easy contrast. It won't write your Position Paper. It won't project the student's own framing onto the stakeholder when the student isn't genuinely taking the perspective — instead, it'll flag the gap: <em>"that's actually your own view talking, not your stakeholder's. Their version of that argument would sound more like…"</em></p>

<h2>Documentation reminder</h2>
<p>Every substantive Stakeholder Voice conversation gets logged in the <a href="/foundations/ai-documentation-protocol/">AI Documentation Template</a>. Section A students additionally document the Boodle Build process — what design choices you made when constructing the bot, which felt authentic, which the bot got wrong when peer-tested.</p>

